title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that checks the total purchases in 2025 from creditors with "VVS" in their name. It must also be creditors that do not have "SLETTET" in their name. Output in descending. I want creditor_id, creditor name and total price of each in my output. Output in textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log: Create a Wayang plan that computes the total purchases in 2025 from creditors whose names contain "VVS" and exclude any creditors whose names contain "SLETTET". For each qualifying creditor, output creditor_id, creditor_name, and total_price, in descending order (by total_price). The final output should be provided as a text file.

log.thoughts: Selected the tables needed for the query: factpurchases for purchase details and creditor for filtering by name and retrieving creditor_id and name.

steps.detailed_description: Load factpurchases and creditor tables as inputs. This provides purchase_line details (invoice_date, invoice_line_price, creditor_id) and creditor metadata (creditor_id, name).

Join the factpurchases dataset with the creditor dataset on creditor_id to attach creditor names to each purchase line. Input: both tables. Output: combined dataset with purchaser details and creditor name.

Filter records to year 2025 based on invoice_date, and retain only creditors whose name contains 'VVS' and does not contain 'SLETTET'. Then aggregate by creditor_id and creditor_name computing total_price as the sum of invoice_line_price for each creditor. Input: joined and filtered purchases. Output: per-creditor total_price records.
Sort the aggregated results by total_price in descending order and write the final output as a text file containing creditor_id, creditor_name, and total_price for each qualifying creditor.

log.thoughts: Two data sources are joined to map creditor names to purchases. Then we filter for 2025 and the name criteria, aggregate totals per creditor, and finally output the sorted results to a text file. This uses 4 steps to keep the plan concise and coherent.

(SELECT creditor_id, name FROM creditor) as X

log.thoughts: Loaded factpurchases and creditor tables as inputs for the planned downstream joins/transformations.
Created first two JDBC inputs for factpurchases and creditor, then a join on creditor_id. Accessed fields from Record as per JDBC behavior.
